This paper deals with wireless communication networks, resource allocation, and fairness, which are all topics that fall under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses cognitive radio networks, which are a subset of wireless networks that involve intelligent spectrum management, making cs.CR another likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes simulations, which could fall under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM) if the simulations involve multimedia data.
